{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_oliver_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280600544/1930110801/0204.xml":{"full_text":"UTILITIES FEATURE\nACTIVE CURB MART\n\u2666Selling Side Predominates at\nShort Session\u2014New\nLows Recorded.\nBY JOHN A. CItONE.\n\u2022aeeLi Dispatch to The Star.\nNEW YORK. November 8 \u2014Public\nUtilities featured active curb trading\ntoday. Cities Service led the down\nswing aa it broke about three points\nafter opening with a block of 33,800\nShares at 20Vfc. a new low.\nElectric Bond A Share, in point of\nAape interest, waa eclipsed by Cities\nThe former opened with a\nblock of 6,000 share* at 4t%, off\nand moved thereafter within a frac\ntional range.\nh The feature of the opening was the\n53,800-share block of Cities Service,\nrepresenting hundreds of bunched\norders. In the hectic November days of\n1129, Cities Service established a curb\nopening record when 225.000 shares ap\npeared at 41%. Today's Initial sale,\nhowever, was one of the largest open\nings since last January.\nA planned bear attack in Boston\noarly Friday afternoon started the\npresent selling movement in Cities\nService. The Boston specialist was so\noverwhelmed with orders that he had\n\u2022to ask for a temporary suspension until\n\u2022he straightened out his book. Wall\nStreet within a few minutes heard that\nilmilar situation had developed in\nChicago and traders Jumped to the\nconclusion that similar action had\nbeen taken here, but trading in Cities\nService was not suspended on the curb\n\u00abt any time Friday.\nScores of new lows were registered\n'by the utilities in the first hour to\nday. They included Associated Gas,\nAmerican Cities Power A Light B,\nAmerican Gas A Electric,. Amerl\nt Light A Traction, American\nirpower, Central States Electric,\nolid a ted Oas of Baltimore, Elec-\nBond A Share. Middle West trtil-\nNlag&ra Shares. Tampa Electric\nStandard Power A Light B.\nnnroad Corporation, after opening\n\u00abn 5,000 shares at 7, had no trouble\nbreaking into new low ground at 6%.\nFennroad has an investment in Sea\nboard approximating 409,000 shares.\nStandard Oils were hammered right\nfrom the opening gong. Standard\nOil of Indiana and Standard of Ken\ntucky fell to hew lows early in the\nsession. Cos den. Gulf, Indian Territory\nIlluminating, a subsidiary of Cities\nService, and other active miscellaneous\npetroleums reached new minimum quo\ntations for the year or longer.\nNatural gas shares Were not spared\nm the general wave of selling. Arkan\nsas Natural Gas A, a subsidiary of\nCities Service, was the first to hit a\nn*W low mark, but Lone Star Natural\nGas and United Gas soon joined it\nBONES ON TUB CUEB\nMARKET.\nMies la DOUflmc BONDS\nufiiutsnds. High. Low. close.\nlAm Omwlh PW Si 40 93 |6 99\n8% 8* 8a\n\"v Amer PM, is\n9 BpeUch Po* Ss '54 IQIV4 10? V\u00ab 181 V.\n3jj% I S,, 'L\n,s ,8\nJlfecdlf'P\nnJgffli.VJfe.'tMS lift Bit B*s\n7 Clt sere Ou Ss *p B 88' SS'\n1 Clt Ber Oas P Ss *4s H% 12% 91%\nscat Serv Pw 5%\u00bb 's* 85 83% 83%\n2 Comwlh Ed 4s B #0 100 100 100\nSS Consum Pow 4%s \u20199B H% *9% \u00a79%\n188 Com G 4 t il A H 94% 83% 84\nOpntinen Oil 5%s '37 W% 94% 9\u00ab%\n11 Elec PftL Ss A 3030 85% 85 *5\nis Empire OAR s'4s 88% 85% 85%\n1 Gatineau Pow Ss '54, 94 94 34\naoien Laund S%s \u201937. 38 38 38\n\u2022l Oeoreta PoWer 58 '*7 10S% 100 100\n1 Grand P4W Ss 43.. 35 35 85\nJ Grind Trunk '33 107% 107% 107%\nS Gulf St Util it A \u2019M 99% 99% 99%\n1 Sous OuU O Is A '43 90% #O% 30%\nlflfinoUP *Vl%s $93 8 51\njfSSSSflfeAlWio 0 1 I JL\nfiK'rraii a H E*\n7 Intern Sec Am 5s '47 7|% 78% 7|A4\n5 intersta Power Is '52 M 96 10\nII laves Co Ss A \u201947 J\u00bb 71% W% 3%\n\"I fiiv to it A *47 xw. 73 73 73\nJ Jers CPM sVis A '45 102 102 102.\nto Kelvtnator it if xw 83% S 3 33%\nKoppers ofcSi '47 99% M H.\nit\u00ae =8 11*! ife B\nP\ntMld* d W\u00bbst Util sis' '32. 101% 100% 100%\n'PHEif Eli\npEfwIII 11 .Ik: Mi\niss:{ r mris is* if 4 ijr\n:.gisasKv h h 5a\nIDKTPIL 4%S 17.. SI 13%\nIRrVMftY* lg% ifi\u00ab lg%\n3 Northw